𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗺𝗲𝘁𝗵𝗲𝘂𝘀 𝗖𝗼𝗺𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗱𝘀 (𝗗𝗲𝘃𝗢𝗽𝘀)

Prometheus is a leading monitoring and alerting toolkit for modern DevOps environments.

🔹 Check Version & Start
 prometheus --version → Check the installed Prometheus version
 prometheus --config.file=prometheus.yml → Start Prometheus using a specific configuration file
 prometheus --storage.tsdb.path=/data → Specify the storage path for metrics data

🔹 Configuration & Rules Validation
 promtool check config prometheus.yml → Validate the Prometheus configuration file for errors
 promtool check rules rules.yml → Verify alerting or recording rules
 promtool test rules test_rules.yml → Test alerting/recording rules before applying

🔹 API & Metrics Queries
 curl http://localhost:9090/api/v1/targets → List all active scrape targets
 curl http://localhost:9090/api/v1/alerts → View currently active alerts
 curl http://localhost:9090/api/v1/query?query=up → Query specific metric data

🔹 Service Management
 systemctl start prometheus → Start Prometheus service
 systemctl stop prometheus → Stop Prometheus service
 systemctl restart prometheus → Restart Prometheus service
 systemctl status prometheus → Check the status of Prometheus service

🔹 Logs & Monitoring
 journalctl -u prometheus -f → Follow Prometheus logs in real-time
